text: Seletar Airport in Singapore is a local airport located 16 kilometres northwest from the Changi Airport, the country's main airport. Seletar Airport is originally operated in 1928 known as RAF Seletar, military airbase of the British Royal Air Force. In 1971, the base was handed back to Singapore and now mostly serves turbo-prop and smaller-sized private and business jet. == References == Category:Buildings and structures in Singapore Category:Airports in Asia
